1. Synopsis

   bboTS is a free team switching client. It can be used to automatically
   switch users currently playing on a Call of Duty: Black Ops server and
   currently using a specified TeamSpeak3 Server to designated channels.
   bboTS can be used on any platform supporting Java6.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

2. Features

    * Switch users on a TS3 server depending on their current Black Ops team.
    * Uses EJTS3ServerQuery library to connect to the TeamSpeak3 server.
    * Uses the Call of Duty: Black Ops RCon protocol to communicate with the
      game server.
    * ...
    ___________________________________________________________________________

3. Installation

   If you only want to run bboTS you can use the provided stable packages. A
   detailed HowTo can be found at https://github.com/bb-generation/bboTS/wiki/Install-bboTS
   Otherwise if you want to install it from source please read chapter 3.2
    ___________________________________________________________________________

3.1. Dependencies

    * Oracle Java6

   If you want to install from source you additionally need
    * git
    * Javadoc
    * Apache Ant
    ___________________________________________________________________________

3.2. Install from source

   1. `git clone git://github.com/bb-generation/bboTS.git`
   2. `mkdir config`
   3. `cp config.examples/*.properties config/`
   4. Configure bboTS as seen in https://github.com/bb-generation/bboTS/wiki/Install-bboTS
   5. `ant run`
    ___________________________________________________________________________

4. More Information

   This program was originally written because there was no option to change
   teams on a Black Ops Ranked Server.
   But bboTS is alse useful for playing on an Unranked Server, e.g. if you
   don't care about who is playing with whom on a training session.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

4.1 How to report bugs

   Bugs can be filed as issues at the Github Issue Tracker at
   https://github.com/bb-generation/bboTS/issues or submitted
   directly to us at bbots@bbgen.net.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

4.2. How to get involved

   If you are a Java developer and would like to help us develope this library
   please take a look at our Github Project at
   https://github.com/bb-generation/bboTS
   If you have implemented a new feature, just create a new Issue and attach
   your patch to it. Take a look at HACKING for further details.
    ___________________________________________________________________________

